a:a.name: DESC
a:a.a:v:
EN:

Configuration of the Port module.

a:a.name: DESC
a:a.a:v:
EN:

VariantPreCompile: Only precompile time configuration parameters. Only one set of parameters. VariantPostBuild: Mix of precompile and postbuild time configuration parameters. Only one set of parameters. If Config Variant = VariantPreCompile, the files Port_Cfg.h and Port_Cfg.c should be used. If Config Variant = VariantPostBuild, the files Port_Cfg.h and Port_PBcfg.c should be used.

a:tst.true: For Variant PreCompile, only 1 ' PortConfigSet ' should exist.

a:a.name: DESC
a:a.a:v:
EN:

This container contains a configuration of the PORT driver / SIUL module. This container is a MultipleConfigurationContainer, i.e. this container and its sub-containers exit once per configuration set. NOTE:"User may configure only ONE instance of PortConfigSet container due to single Port_Init() call allowed."

a:a.name: DESC
a:a.a:v:
EN:

The init parameters values for the notused pins in the PORT configuration.

a:a.name: DESC
a:a.a:v:
EN:

Enable Weak Pull Up/Down for the configured Pin. Checked box means any of the Weak Pull Up or Weak Pull Down configurations is enabled for the pin. This is an implementation specific parameter.

a:tst.true: Configure as input pin must enable internal wake pull up or down.

a:a.name: DESC
a:a.a:v:
EN:

Select Weak Pull Up/Down for the configured Pin. Checked box means the Weak Pull Up configuration is set. Unchecked box means the Weak Pull Down configuration is set. This is an implementation specific parameter.

a:a.name: DESC
a:a.a:v:
EN:

Enable Open Drain Output for the configured Pin. Checked box means the Open Drain configuration is set. This is an implementation specific parameter.

a:a.name: DESC
a:a.a:v:
EN:

Selects the initial direction of the pin (IN or OUT). If the direction is not changeable, the value configured here is fixed. The pin direction can be set only for the GPIO pins. For the Alternative Function modes the OUT pin direction is hw selected. If the IN direction is needed too, it can be set at runtime. NOTE: To set the IN direction take care, please, that all the possible module inputs, possible as Alternative Functions for the pad mode, are hw connected together, if IN direction is enabled, to the pad.

a:a.name: DESC
a:a.a:v:
EN:

Port Pin Level value from Port pin list.

a:a.a:v:
EN:

Container collecting the PortPins.

a:a.name: DESC
a:a.a:v:
EN:

The number of specified PortPins in this PortContainer.

a:tst.false: For calculating the correct value use the CALC button

a:a.name: DESC
a:a.a:v:
EN:

Configuration of the individual port pins.

a:a.name: DESC
a:a.a:v:
EN:

Enable Weak Pull Up/Down for the configured Pin. Checked box means any of the Weak Pull Up or Weak Pull Down configurations is enabled for the pin. This is an implementation specific parameter.

a:a.name: DESC
a:a.a:v:
EN:

Select Weak Pull Up/Down for the configured Pin. Checked box means the Weak Pull Up configuration is set. Unchecked box means the Weak Pull Down configuration is set. This is an implementation specific parameter.

a:a.name: DESC
a:a.a:v:
EN:

Enable Open Drain Output for the configured Pin. Checked box means the Open Drain configuration is set. This is an implementation specific parameter.

a:a.name: DESC
a:a.a:v:
EN:

Enable/Disable Safe Mode for the pin. Checked box means the Safe Mode is enabled.

a:a.name: DESC
a:a.a:v:
EN:

Enables/Disables the read back possibility for this pin. Checked box means the Read Back is enabled. When ReadBack is enabled, the Input Bufer of the pin gets enabled by setting the IBE bit in the MSCR (PCR) of the pin. Some alternate functions working as inputs might require having the IBE set to 1, so check this box in order to achieve this.

a:a.name: DESC
a:a.a:v:
EN:

Enable input hysteresis for the associated pin. Checked box means Hysteresis configurations is enabled for the pin. This is an implementation specific parameter.

a:a.name: DESC
a:a.a:v:
EN:

Enable/Disable the changeability for the configured Pin. Checked box means the Direction Changeability is enabled. This is an implementation specific parameter. The changeable pin direction can be set only for the GPIO pins. For a mode different than GPIO, pin direction changeablity shall be disabled.

a:a.name: DESC
a:a.a:v:
EN:

Parameter to indicate if the mode of a port pin is changeable during runtime. True: Port Pin mode changeable allowed. False: Port Pin mode changeable not permitted The function for changing the pin modes is not supported by the safety implementation.

a:a.name: DESC
a:a.a:v:
EN:

Pin Id of the port pin. This value will be assigned to the symbolic name derived from the port pin container short name.

a:tst.false: The value of PortPinId is not unique for this configuration.
The value of PortPinId can't be higher than the number of defined pins

a:a.name: DESC
a:a.a:v:
EN:

Used to specify port configuration register: SIUL I/O Pin Multiplexed Signal Configuration Registers (MSCR number).

a:tst.true: Invalid Pin number for current package

a:tst.false: PortPinPcr is repeated for two or more ports. Use the Calc button to calculate correct default value.

a:tst.true: Invalid Pin number for current package

a:a.name: DESC
a:a.a:v:
EN:

Selects the direction of the pin (IN, OUT or both) that will be configured by Port_Init() function if the pin is configured as GPIO. If the direction is not changeable, the value configured here is fixed. For the Alternative Function modes (PortPinMode is different than GPIO), the setting in this enumeration control is kept in the port configuration structure and it is used when Port_SetPinMode() is called at runtime to change the mode of the pin to GPIO. If your Alternative Function is an input functionality that requires the IBE bit to be set in the MSCR, please select the checkbox 'PortPinWithReadback.

a:tst.true: For pads in Analog Input mode the PortPinDirection value shall be set to PORT_PIN_IN
For pads in Only Input mode the PortPinDirection value shall be set to PORT_PIN_IN

a:a.name: DESC
a:a.a:v:
EN:

Port pin mode from mode list for use with Port_Init() function. NOTE: This parameter is not used in the current implementation and is retained as per std AUTOSAR_EcucParamDef.arxml file.

a:a.name: DESC
a:a.a:v:
EN:

Selects the PORT pin mode from the modes list. One or more modes may be valid for a pin. This way it is possible to select between multiple modes.( e.g. DIO (GPIO option) or ICU (eTimer option)).

a:tst.false: PortPinMode repeated for two or more ports. The only mode that can be repeated for Pins is GPIO

a:a.name: DESC
a:a.a:v:
EN:

Port Pin Level value from Port pin list.

a:a.name: DESC
a:a.a:v:
EN:

Configure Slew Rate for the configured Pin. This is an implementation specific parameter.

a:a.name: DESC
a:a.a:v:
EN:

The function for changing the pin modes is not supported by the safety implementation.

a:a.name: DESC
a:a.a:v:
EN:

Pre-processor switch to enable/disable the API to read out the modules version information.

a:a.name: LABEL
a:a.value: Port SetPinMode Does Not Touch GPIO Levels

a:a.name: DESC
a:a.a:v:
EN:

Pre-processor switch. When not checked, the function Port_SetPinMode() will set the output level of the pin to the value configured in the PortPinLevelValue combo when called at run time to change mode of a pin from alternate function to GPIO. When checked, the function Port_SetPinMode() will not touch the output level of the pin when called at run time to change mode of a pin from alternate function to GPIO.

a:a.name: DESC
a:a.a:v: EN:<html> When this parameter is enabled, the Port module will adapt to run from User Mode, with the following measures:<p/> a) configuring REG_PROT for SIUL2 IP so that the registers under protection can be accessed from user mode by setting UAA bit in REG_PROT_GCR to 1<p/> b) using 'call trusted function' stubs for all internal function calls that access registers requiring supervisor mode.<p/> for more information, please see chapter 5.7 User Mode Support in IM <p/> Note: Implementation Specific Parameter. </html>

a:a.name: DESC
a:a.a:v:
EN:

In driver modules which can be instantiated several times on a single ECU, BSW00347 requires that the name of APIs is extended by the VendorId and a vendor specific name. This parameter is used to specify the vendor specific name. In total, the implementation specific name is generated as follows: <ModuleName>_>VendorId>_<VendorApiInfix><Api name from SWS>. E.g. assuming that the VendorId of the implementor is 123 and the implementer chose a VendorApiInfix of "v11r456" a api name Can_Write defined in the SWS will translate to Can_123_v11r456Write. This parameter is mandatory for all modules with upper multiplicity > 1. It shall not be used for modules with upper multiplicity =1.

a:a.name: DESC
